  <span id="freeText16924179986196575829" style="display:none">Who knew that the police in Nigeria <a href="http://news.bbc.co.uk/2/hi/africa/3556740.stm" rel="nofollow noopener">rent out</a> their standard issue weapons to criminals, to pursue illegal activities in the night? Ha! That and many more unknown facets of reality in this gem of a book.<br /><br />I have read by now, a bunch of books by the good Dr. Dalrymple. His criticism of the current sociocultural milieu of Britain is beautifully composed, to say the least. I admire his willingness to go against the grain, which years of experience - as a psychiatric doctor in an English slum - must have bolstered.<br /><br />I have reviewed his other works on goodreads before, but I must reiterate: given the numerous accusations of elitism and apathy against him; the author displays the classic case of heartfelt consideration turning sour – into abject cynicism.</span>
